text.section:
An authority may:
Accept grants or other funds or property from any source, public or private;
Enter into such contractual relationships as may be necessary;
Acquire real property, by gift or devise or by purchase pursuant to the provisions of KRS 45A.045, and hold the same in the name of the Commonwealth for the use and benefit of the authority;
Adopt rules and regulations necessary to the performance of its duties and functions.
